cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and privacy, specifically the mutual information between two random variables and the amount of information leaked about one of them through an additive Gaussian channel. This falls under the scope of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses approximation techniques and estimation-theoretic quantities, which are common in machine learning and statistics, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper mentions an operational interpretation of data privacy, which could potentially fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
